rComments: Very understanding of student's needs and will make sure you get extensions if you were sick or having hard time in class. Very nice and supportive.

Firstly, Melissa is a really genuine teacher.  She is very upfront about expectations which is good because it lets you know what you need to do to do well in the course.  She is also flexible if you ask her about going off topic a little and want to explore something different in your final paper.

Didn't like her at first- thought she was going to be strict and difficult but turns out she really cares and will help you out if you are willing to work. She's very nice but she doesn't look like a prof!

Marked hard for first assignment and the second assignment I got a really good mark.  Tutorials are boring and she just goes over assignments.  I agree that she is a lot better in office hours- she will tell you how to get an A and if you follow her advice she gives you good mark.
Tutorials are boring because they are only for explaining assignments.  When I see her at her office hours she is much more helpful.
will help you out if you go to her office hours.  nice teacher and fair marker.
